    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what Proverbs 20 says to what it means — tracing the author's intent in its original canonical context, locating the chapter's argument within the wisdom tradition, and noting where it reaches forward into the New Testament. The movements below group the chapter's thirty proverbs into their thematic clusters rather than treating each verse in isolation. Where Hebrew nuance materially changes the English, a brief note supplements the exposition.",
